# Project 3 - AI & Autonomous Weapons, Decade of Growth in the Government

My hunch is that a few AI & Automation focused firms have had explosive growth in government contracts in the last decade. I want to show that by grabbing all of the USAspeanding.gov info on Anduril, Palantir, Sheild AI, a few others to track their growth over time and compare their contract values to the traditional Primes like Lockheed Martin.

## My Process 

(1) Getting the Data
- I'm pulling the data from USASpending.gov

(2) Analysis
- I started by inspecting the document in Google Sheets, as it has over 200 columns of data. I slimmed it down to only the essentials & cleaned some company names. 
- I grouped everything by recipeint name, which I cleaned in Google sheets (which has a data diary btw).
- I totalled all contracts as well so we have two operative pieces of data to work with

(3) Buuble Charts
- I knew I wanted to do a bubble chart since getting that particular piece of criticism on my last piece, so I have Claude teach me how, steap by step and I wrote all the code myself, though Claude would explain each piece to me to I can replicate it and explain what every piece does. 
- I created a second bubble charting showing the total of Lockheed's 2025 contracts vs everything else ibn my data set in 2025, though I don't think this one will make it into the final piece. 


